@startuml state-lifecycle
title Matrix lifecycle: open and locked modes

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundCorner 8

[*] --> Open : construct(n_rows, n_cols)

state Open {
    Open : inserts go to per row buffers
    Open : buffer index map (O(1) lookups)
    Open : dirty bitset set on each insert
    Open : reads consult buffer first,\n  fall back to CSR slice if present
}

state "Lock pipeline" as Locking {
    Locking : 1. sort + dedup each row buffer
    Locking : 2. build_csr or merge_csr
    Locking : 3. install per row CSR slices
    Locking : 4. clear buffers per lock_policy
    Locking : 5. clear dirty bitset
}

state Locked {
    Locked : CSR is the authoritative store
    Locked : reads are O(log k) per row slice
    Locked : inserts throw logic_error
    Locked : SpMV, SpGEMM, transpose legal
}

Open    --> Locking : lock()
Locking --> Locked  : all rows processed
Locked  --> Open    : open()
Open    --> Open    : insert / get / contains
Locked  --> Locked  : spmv / spgemm / accumulate
Locked  --> [*]     : destruct

note right of Locking
    First lock: build_csr
    Subsequent locks: merge_csr
    + dirty bitset fast path
end note

note right of Open
    compact_preserve: buffers kept, O(1) re-open
    compact_move:     buffers freed, O(n) re-open
    no_compact:       CSR never built
end note

@enduml
